	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Two words: feature creep. If you ever want to get anything done, make sure you never, ever, move the goalposts. Keep it simple, keep it short, and know when to say &quot;IT'S DONE&quot; and kick it out the door.<br /><br />That time is <em>not</em> &quot;good&quot;. Your project will <em>never</em> be &quot;good&quot;. The day you call something you made &quot;good&quot; is the day you stop improving. So settle for &quot;good enough&quot; instead, and make the next project &quot;better&quot;.<br /><br />Sorry for the tryhard post, but that's what worked for me. YMMV.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


